  "instructions": "Build an implementation plan table. Add columns to define the structure, then add rows and fill in cell values. Column types fall into three categories: Non-executable (ne-) columns are filled now during construction and become read-only during execution -- use these for task descriptions, prerequisites, and other plan content. Executable (ex-) columns are left empty now and filled during execution -- use these for evidence, outcomes, signatures, and other execution artifacts. Auto-executed (ae-) columns are evaluated automatically by the system during execution based on rules you define -- use these for acceptance criteria.",
